Parents or Guardians of 8th grade students:
A form went out on April 14, 2020 that read as follows: Although we have not yet determined which students have fulfilled all the requirements for promotion to 9th grade, we are still requesting that the following information be provided to us on or before May 6, 2020. This name verification should be returned preferably via email to gonzaly@msmusd.org if you don’t have email please return it in your student homework packets as soon as possible or leave in our little book house in front of the office. Very important to do so before May 6, 2020. If not received by that date the name used on the certificate will be as it is on Powerschool. No name changes will be done after that date.

Thank you

Yolanda E. Gonzalez

post_text: PCSO performed a very thorough search of the entire school with the assistance of several other agencies. The report of gunshots has been unfounded, there are no injuries reported nor evidence that a gun was actually fired on the campus. PCSO has cleared the campus and declared it safe for a regular school day. Officers will take extra precautions regarding the safety of all students while at school to assure our parents, students, and staff is in a safe environment.

post_text: Mammoth-San Manuel USD had a report by employees that they heard gunshots at the school this evening. Pinal County Sheriffs Office has responded in great force: dogs, helicopters and other law enforcement agencies to clear the school. No reports of injuries at this time. PCSO is taking special precautions to insure the safety of our school and are clearing for a regular school day tomorrow. More information will be provided as it becomes available.

The Mammoth-San Manuel USD #8 is once again seeking pictures of Veterans in the Tri-Community Area for its annual Veteran’s Day Celebration held on November 9, 2018 at 9:30am in the District Auditorium.
Pictures should be scanned from the original and emailed to joliatm@msmusd.org no later than November 2, 2018 to be added to the presentation. Pictures taken of pictures using cell phones are not high enough in quality and therefore do not have a high enough resolution for the computer program. If you don’t have a scanner, take the picture to any school office and they can scan and email it for you.

post_text:
Mammoth-San Manuel USD will continue to have an altered schedule for May 1. Start times all the same, but release times different. We will release students at the Jr. Sr. High at 12:15 (The Reddington students will wait in the office until 1PM for their bus.). First Avenue Elementary will release at 12:45 and Mammoth Elementary will release at 1:10. All students will be fed lunch before the release times.
Family Activity Night for the Junior High (Jumanji Night), scheduled for May 1st, will be cancelled and, if possible, scheduled at a later date.
Continue to check Facebook, REMIND text service, and the marquee for timely updates. Our website has not been updating as fast, we apologize.

post_text:
San Manuel High School is aware of the threat posted to
Facebook that was directed towards an “SHS” school. The threat did not mention a specific school, but the safety of our students is our top priority. The District is taking the necessary steps to ensure the safety of our students.
PCSO has been notified and is monitoring our campus. Gates will remain locked and our staff has been alerted. If you have any questions or concerns please direct them to our District Office at 520-385-2337.

post_text: Please note the MSMUSD has been working very closely on this issue at First Avenue Elementary with the School Facility Board (SFB) who is responsible for paying contractors for this work. The district has been pushing to make this happen. We have continued to contact the contractors to finish the work. Your MSMUSD Board Members and Superintendent allocated funds to temporarily cover the cost of necessary repairs until the SFB releases funds. The contractors have been scheduled for this Monday to continue work on the gas issue so our students can learn in comfort. Everything is being done to rectify this situation as the safety of our students is of utmost importance to us. Feel free to contact the District office with any questions or concerns.

post_text:
Clear Water for San Manuel Jr. Sr. High School

In coordination with the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality, the San Manuel Jr. Sr. High School and the entire district participated in a proactive statewide public school drinking water lead screening program. San Manuel Jr. Sr. High School's results came back below the screening level, as did the rest of district's schools. The only concern was the District Auditorium of which a water fountain was tested (see our website for letter to parents and test results). The water fountain tested is in a location not regularly utilized. Corrective action has been taken to insure the safety of all students as the Schools Facility Board does further testing and needed corrective action to insure the safety of all students.

post_text: The Saddlebrooke Rotary Club had a fundraising event for the art department at First Avenue Elementary and 2 other schools. $2,200 was raised for each school. The event featured Dianna Maderas, a famous painter who resides in Tucson. It also included a 5th grade art contest. Our students’ paintings stood out because of their excellence. Congratulations to Augie Romero who took 1st place and Kiera Boulware who took 2nd place! Along with their ribbons, they each received a book and a gift certificate to the Maderas Gallery in Tucson. Some of the donated money will be put toward creating a mural that we plan to install in our cafeteria.

FREE EDUCATION and OPPORTUNITIES beyond High School!

Joint Technical Education District (JTED) offers premier, tuition-free Career and Technical Education programs to sophomores, juniors and seniors. JTED counselors will be on the San Manuel Jr. Sr. High campus January 10 for a presentation on what JTED has to offer our 10-12 grade students. This will be presented to 9-11 grade and parents. It will be held in room 55. DON’T wait to learn what JTED could offer your son or daughter, act now! Give them an opportunity to leave high school with a certificate, furthering their ability to get a job right after high school or applying those credits towards college.
For a complete listing of outstanding JTED Career & Technical Education programs offered go to pimajted.org or speak with our High School counselor (Terri Simon or Dave Jungbluth @ 385-2336 ext. 2210/2212 or 1104

The Mammoth-San Manuel Unified School District is collecting pictures of our local veterans for the Annual Veteran’s/Patriotism Assembly. Pictures should be e-mailed to joliatm@msmusd.org in order to be part of the slideshow. Pictures that have been turned in the last several years still remain in the slideshow; the goal is to increase our pictures! Pictures may also be dropped off to any of the school offices.

The Mammoth-San Manuel Unified School District is holding its Annual Veteran’s/Patriotism Assembly on Thursday, November 10, 2016 at 915am in the District Auditorium. Community members are encouraged to attend.

• Social Security Number

• Driver License number

post_text:
San Manuel Jr./Sr. High School Registration Info:
Seniors & Juniors: Wednesday, July 27th 8:00 a.m.-11:00a.m.
Sophomores & Freshmen: Thursday, July 28th 8:00 a.m.-11:00a.m.
Junior High (7th & 8th): Friday, July 29th 8:00 a.m.-11:00a.m. and 1:00 p.m.-3:00 p.m.

Class Fees:
Art: $10.00
Autos: $10.00
Welding: $10.00
Woods: $10.00

Sports Fees:
1st Sport: $30.00
2nd Sport:$25.00
3rd Sport:$20.00

Please make sure all contact information including address, phone numbers and emergency contacts are up to date and correct. As a reminder, we can only release information to the legal parents or guardians.

MEET YOUR TEACHER
Teachers will be available for students on Friday, July 29 from 8 a.m. to 11:00 a.m.

Arizona State Statute requires all students to have a certified copy of a birth certificate on file, proof of immunizations as well as proof of residency (bill or driver's license) before we can register your child.

Oracle students must bring a "Certificate of Residency" each year prior to being allowed to register. This document if available at the Oracle District Office

STATE SOFTBALL INFORMATION:

2016 ADMISSION PRICE

Rose Mofford &Arizona State University:

$5.00 High School Students with ID !!!!!

$10.00 Adults

Fans that have their ticket stub and an AIA hand stamp from the same day AIA softball tournament game will be given free entry into the same day AIA baseball tournament game.

FAN PARKING

Please park east of 25th Avenue in the Rose Mofford Softball Complex until the parking lot is full. The over full parking will be at the Black Canyon Conference Center and along West Mountain View Street. Do not park in the Sanford Brown College or the Corporate Center Property parking lots on weekdays or you be subject to being towed. Those parking lots will be available for weekend parking only.
